Peru Stocks: Cerro Verde, Maple, Panoro, Southern Copper, Volcan

-- B y   A l e x   E m e r y
-- 
2011-08-31T17:29:00Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-08-31/peru-stocks-cerro-verde-maple-panoro-southern-copper-volcan.html
The following companies are having
unusual price changes in  Peru  trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and share prices are as of 1:14 p.m.  New York  time.  The Lima General Index rose for a third session, gaining
2.8 percent to 20,555.23. The MSCI All Peru Capped Index climbed
1.3 percent to 2,699.62.  Mining companies surged after  Standard & Poor’s  raised
Peru’s foreign debt rating to BBB from BBB- and metals prices
advanced, Jose Luis Bustamante, head of trading at Cartisa SAB,
said in a telephone interview.  Panoro Minerals Ltd. (PML)  , a Canadian gold and copper
exploration company, rose 6.7 percent to 48 cents.  Rio Cristal
Resources Corp. (RCZ)  , a Canadian zinc exploration company,
gained 6.3 percent to 17 cents.  Southern Copper Corp. (SCCO)  ,
Peru’s biggest copper producer, climbed 5.5 percent to $34.30.
Volcan Cia. Minera SAA (VOLCABC1 PE), Peru’s largest zinc
producer, rose for a fourth session, adding 4.4 percent to 2.97
soles. Sociedad Minera Cerro Verde SA (CVERDEC1 PE), a unit of
Freeport-McMoRan Copper & Gold Inc., gained 3.8 percent to
$40.05.  Fuel refiners gained after crude futures in New York
advanced.  Refineria la Pampilla SA (RELAPAC1 PE), a unit of  Spain ’s
Repsol YPF SA known as Relapasa, rose 5 percent to 84 centimos.
 Maple Energy Plc (MPLE)  , the oil and natural gas producer
with operations in Peru, gained 2.8 percent to $1.12.  To contact the reporter on this story:
 Alex Emery  in  Lima  at 
 aemery1@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
